title: Jane Austen and the English Landscape (Art Ebook).pdf
description:
Jane Austen and the English Landscape
Barn Elms Publishing | 1996 | ISBN: 1556523068 | English | 144 pages | PDF | 22.4 MB

Landscape historian Batey explores real and fictional settings of Austen's novels. In each chapter she uses a different Austen novel to discuss the style of gardens and landscapes during the early 19th century and Regency England. A continuing theme is the tension between Georgian propriety and the challenging Romantic ideals as they played out in the English landscape. Photos and reproductions of paintings supplement the text
